        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 3 at 7:08PM CDT until June 3 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 708 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Caddo, or 14
miles north of Ranger, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Gordon around 750 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Mingus,
Strawn, Lone Camp, and Thurber.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection stay inside a sturdy structure and keep away from
windows.</instruction>
